                   <h3>The Lincoln Memorial</h3>
                   <p>An American national memorial built to honor the 16th President of the United States, Abraham Lincoln. It is on the western end of the National Mall in Washington, D.C. The architect was Henry Bacon; the designer of the statue, Daniel Chester French. It is a symbol of unity, strength, and wisdom.</p>
