                   <h3>The Washington Monument</h3>
                   <p>An obelisk on the National Mall in Washington, D.C., built to commemorate George Washington. Standing at 555 feet, it was the tallest structure in the world upon its completion in 1884 and remains a central icon of the city, honoring the first President of the United States.</p>
               </div>
